text.__SUMMARY__: Banksia shuttleworthiana, commonly known as bearded dryandra, is a shrub endemic to Western Australia, and is found between the towns of Geraldton and Gingin. It was known as Dryandra shuttleworthiana until 2007, when all Dryandra species were transferred to Banksia by Austin Mast and Kevin Thiele.
